FBIS3-60030 "jptdd002__l94028" JPRS-TDD-94-002-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 11 January 1994 EAST ASIA THAILAND Two Americans, One Barbadian Arrested for Heroin Possession BK0801134294 Hong Kong AFP in English 1330 GMT 8 Jan 94 BK0801134294 Hong Kong AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Bangkok, Jan 8 (AFP)--Two Americans and a Barbados national were arrested Saturday on charges of possessing and trafficking heroin, police said. The two Americans, identified as Yahya Ali Salim, 41, John Charles Hulten, 29, and Daniel Game Mungah, 28, from Barbados, were arrested in downtown Bangkok when police stopped a taxi they were traveling in. Police said they seized 1.3 kilograms (2.86 pounds) of heroin. In Thailand convicted drug traffickers face death penalty, but the sentence is usually commuted to a lengthy prison term. About two-thirds of the 1,200 foreigners in Thai jails have been jailed for drug offences.
